<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She returned to her reality TV roots for MTV's reboot last year of The Hills: New Beginnings.</p>

<p>But with filming for a second season on hold due to the coronavirus pandemic, Whitney Port has been spending more time with her family.</p>

<p>The 35-year-old was seen out and about Monday morning in LA with husband Tim Rosenman and their three-year-old son Sonny. </p>

<p>Laid back outing: The Hills: New beginnings star Whitney Port, 35, was seen out and about Monday morning in LA with husband Tim Rosenman and their three-year-old son Sonny</p>

<p>The trio put on a very laid back show in their casual clothing.</p>

<p>Whitney was dressed in a long and baggy pale green sweatshirt which she paired with loose-fitting black and white horizontally-striped pants. </p>

<p>Hubby Tim wore a pale blue sweatshirt and calf-length baggy beige shorts, and covered up with a dark green cloth face mask in accordance with California's coronavirus regulations.</p>

<p>Sonny had on a long-sleeve top and trousers and held onto both his parents' hands as they walked along.</p>

<p>Casual: Whitney was dressed in a long and baggy, slightly rumpled pale green sweatshirt which she paired with loose-fitting black and white horizontally-striped pants</p>

<p>Port met Rosenman when he served as a producer on another of her reality shows The City and the two tied the knot in 2015. </p>

<p>The reality TV star has candidly shared with her social media followers that she's conflicted about whether to have a second child. </p>

<p>'I know deep down I would like to have another baby. I want Sonny to have another sibling. I feel it would complete our family,' she said on a recent episode of her podcast With Whit. </p>

<p>However, she admitted: 'I really don't feel in a mentally stable place to get pregnant right now.'</p>

<p>She added that due to all the restrictions and rules in place due to COVID-19, 'the thought of having a baby right now, terrifies me'.  </p>

<p>Trio: Port met Rosenman when he served as a producer on another of her reality shows The City and the two tied the knot in 2015. They welcomed their son in 2017 </p>
